OL,6,F"It's time for policymakers to end the
OL,7,Flottery of learning to read by
OL,8,Fcommitting to provide evidence-based
OL,9,Finstruction in all schools," says
OL,10,Fcognitive psychologist Professor Kathy
OL,11,FRastle.
OL,13,F"Overwhelming evidence"
OL,15,FDecades of scientific research has
OL,16,Fshown that virtually all children can
OL,17,Flearn to read if taught in line with
OL,18,Fthe evidence. Despite this, illiteracy
OL,19,Frates in the UK have remained
OL,20,Fstubbornly high for more than a
OL,21,Fcentury.
