OL,4,Cteaching method after failings in Wales
OL,6,FIn Wales in particular, the figures
OL,7,Fare shocking. The schools' watchdog,
OL,8,FEstyn, says up to 30% of Welsh
OL,9,Fchildren start secondary school unable
OL,10,Fto use basic English reading skills
OL,11,Fwell.
OL,13,FFor most of the twentieth century,
OL,14,FBritish children were taught to read
OL,15,Fusing a mixture of phonics - which
OL,16,Fteaches the relationships between
OL,17,Fletters and sounds - and cueing.
