OL,6,FDecades ago scientists found that only
OL,7,Fone of these methods is effective for
OL,8,Fthe act of reading words, known as
OL,9,Fdecoding. Using both approaches can
OL,10,Feven be damaging, as teaching children
OL,11,Fto use cues can undermine phonics
OL,12,Fteaching.
OL,14,F"There is overwhelming evidence that
OL,15,Fchildren need to understand that
OL,16,Fletters stand for sounds, and that the
OL,17,Fbest way to teach this is through
OL,18,Fsystematic phonics," Professor Rastle
OL,19,Fof Royal Holloway University tells me.
