OL,6,FIn 2005, frustrated with a lack of
OL,7,Fimprovement in reading levels despite
OL,8,Frecord investment in schools, the
OL,9,FLabour government launched a
OL,10,Fparliamentary inquiry into the
OL,11,Fteaching of early reading. Retired
OL,12,Fheadteacher and former Ofsted Chief
OL,13,FInspector Sir Jim Rose concluded that
OL,14,Fthe old system of using both phonics
OL,15,Fand cueing should be replaced with
OL,16,Fusing systematic synthetic phonics.
