OL,6,FThe most common programme used to
OL,7,Fteach reading in primary schools in
OL,8,FScotland is called Active Literacy.
OL,9,FThe government paid North Lanarkshire
OL,10,FCouncil more than #1.1m to develop it
OL,11,Fmore than a quarter of a century ago.
OL,12,FThe programme encourages children to
OL,13,F"look at the pictures" to read words
OL,14,Fif they are stuck.
OL,16,FGillian Evans' son Thomas was taught
OL,17,Fto read using Active Literacy in his
OL,18,FSouth Ayrshire primary school. While
OL,19,FThomas' twin sister excelled at
OL,20,Freading, Thomas did not.
