OL,6,FWhen she raised concerns, Gillian was
OL,7,Ftold that "boys are slower than girls"
OL,8,Fso she should be more firm with him
OL,9,Fand "wait and see". Years later,
OL,10,FThomas was diagnosed with
OL,11,Fdevelopmental dyslexia, dysgraphia and
OL,12,FADHD.
OL,14,F"All the concerns we had are the early
OL,15,Fsigns of these conditions," said
OL,16,FGillian, "but no professional teacher
OL,17,Fin an accredited dyslexia friendly
OL,18,Fschool warned us that Thomas was at
OL,19,Frisk of literacy failure if he was not
OL,20,Fgiven the correct teaching
OL,21,Finstruction."
