OL,6,F"He was set up to fail", Gillian tells
OL,7,Fme, "every day he went in to school
OL,8,Fand the teachers were not teaching him
OL,9,Fwhat I later learned was decoding. He
OL,10,Fdid not know how to decode words to
OL,11,Fread them, and he was taught to guess."
OL,13,FThomas's story is not unique. Reading
OL,14,Fexperts believe that while some
OL,15,Fchildren learn to read adequately
OL,16,Fregardless of the method of teaching,
OL,17,Fmany need explicit and systematic
OL,18,Fphonics instruction.
