OL,6,FThese struggling readers often come
OL,7,Ffrom disadvantaged backgrounds where
OL,8,Fthey don't read at home or have a
OL,9,Fspecific reading challenge like
OL,10,Fdyslexia. For these children, cueing
OL,11,Fcan undermine their reading progress.
OL,13,F"We can't just immerse them in books,"
OL,14,Fsays Geraldine Millar, Headteacher of
OL,15,FSt Ninian's Primary School in Glasgow,
OL,16,F"we have to teach them the code and
OL,17,Fthat unlocks everything."
