OL,6,F"Many teachers struggle to meet the
OL,7,Fspecific needs of struggling readers,"
OL,8,Fsaid Dr Law, "often because they don't
OL,9,Fhave access to research-based methods
OL,10,Ffor reading instruction.
OL,12,F"That's why it's so important to
OL,13,Fprovide educators with thorough
OL,14,Fprofessional development`giving them
OL,15,Fthe knowledge and tools they need to
OL,16,Fhelp every student succeed in reading."
OL,18,FProfessor Kathy Rastle of Royal
OL,19,FHolloway University, says reading is
OL,20,F"too important to be left to chance."
